initiate the attack and during.  This skills usefullness
varies with class.

#
ARMORCRAFT
Help for &2"Armorcraft"&n 

&3Level&n: 20
&3Usage&n: &4repair <armor name>&n
&3Class&n: Thief, Warrior, Priest, Nightblade, Battlemage, 
       Spellsword, Paladin, Master

This skill allows you to repair non-magic armor when it is
damaged.  Once mastered the skill will always repair the
armor.  It is also a pre-requisite to the repair facility.
#
"CLOT WOUNDS"
Help for &2"Clot Wounds"&n

&3Level&n: 25
&3Usage&n: &4clot <victim>&n
&3Class&n: Cleric, Druid, Priest, Paladin, Master

This skill is a higher level healing skill that the healers 
are able to utilise once practiced.  This also has a limit 
of 5 uses in 3 tics of game play.  This skill will heal 5*level 
to a max of 400hps per usage.

See Also: Attend Wounds; First Aid
#
"DARK RITUAL"
Help for &2"Dark Ritual"&n

&3Level&n: 40
&3Usage&n: &4dark ritual&n
&3Class&n: Magician, Druid, Battlemage, Spellsword, Master

As it's name suggest, this is a skill that should only be 
performed by those of evil alignment. Good or neutral 
characters may suffer adverse affects. If you are successful
in performing this ritual, you will exchange some of your life
force (HP) for magic reserves (MP).
#
"FIRST AID"
Help for &2"First Aid"&n

&3Level&n: 1
&3Usage&n: &4first <victim>&n
&3Class&n: Cleric, Druid, Priest, Paladin, Master

This skill is a basic healing skill that enables the healers 
to heal a player or themselves with 2*level to a max of 50hps. 
It is also limited to 5 uses in 3 tics of game play.

See Also: Clot Wounds, Attend Wounds.
#
FLYTACKLE
Help for &2"Flying Tackle"&n

&3Level&n   : 45
&3Usage&n   : &4flytackle <victim>&n
&3Duration&n: 3 round wait before next usage
&3Class&n   : Thief, Warrior, Priest, Nightblade, Battlemage, Spellsword,
          Paladin, Master

This skill allows you to initiate the attack with a flying
tackle that sends the victim to the ground if succesfull.
#
BERSERK
Help for &2"Berserk"&n

&3Level&n   : 35 (TODO)
&3Usage&n   : &4berserk&n
&3Duration&n: Length of Combat
&3Class&n   : Warrior, Master

If successful, you will enter a battle frenzy that will 
last until the fight is over. Whilst in this frenzy, you 
will do twice the damage and receive only half 
(Depending on effectiveness). However, you will not be 
able to cast any spells whilst berserk.
#
COMPOST
Help for &2"Compost"&n

&3Level&n: 35
&3Usage&n: &4compost corpse&n
&3Class&n: Magician, Druid, Battlemage, Spellsword, Master

This skill allows the player to turn corpses into small
mounds of compost, thus profiting by receiving a small
amount of mana in return. It can not be performed on
player corpses.
#
"TRAP PIT"
Help for &2"Trap Pit"&n

&3Level&n: 25
&3Usage&n: &4trap pit&n
&3Class&n: Thief, Priest, Nightblade, Spellsword, Master

This skill allows pit traps to be set.  These have a random chance of
activating when a character (player or otherwise) leaves the room the trap is
set in.

Damage is determined by the class, level and dexterity of the trapper.

Pit traps may only be set outoors, not underwater, and not in mid air.

See Also: Trap, Trap Magic.
#
"TRAP MAGIC"
Help for &2"Trap Magic"&n

&3Level&n: 25
&3Usage&n: &4trap magic&n
&3Class&n: Priest, Spellsword, Master

This skill allows magic traps to be set.  These have a random chance of
activating when a character (player or otherwise) leaves the room the trap is
set in.

When this trap is triggered, a random spell will be fired at the victim. This
will most likely be a damaging spell, but not always.  Also, where possible, 
the victim will be blinded for a short period of time.

Magic traps may be set anywhere other than in mid-air.

See also: Trap, Trap Pit.
#
"POISON BLADE"
Help for &2"Poison Blade"&n

&3Level&n   : 40
&3Usage&n   : &4poison blade&n
&3Duration&n: &42 tics&n
&3Class&n   : Magician, Druid, Battlemage, Spellsword, Master

Once called this will poison your weilded bladed weapon.
The only draw back is finding a suitable container to
hold the poison in.

#
SLIP
Help for &2"Slip"&n

&3Level&n: 15
&3Usage&n: &4slip <object> <victim>&n
&3Class&n: Thief, Priest, Nightblade, Spellsword, Master

This skill is used to give itmes to the target unnoticed.
The item to be given must be in your inventory.  You can 
also drop items quietly by using this skill at an item
only.
#
